-- Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Air Mauritius, Oando of Nigeria Move
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-05-25T15:38:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-air-mauritius-oando-of-nigeria-move.html
Kenya’s  All-Share Index (NSEASI)  fell for a
second day, dropping 1.2 percent to 63.55 in Nairobi, the lowest
close since May 11.  Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index (SEMDEX)  snapped three days of declines,
rising less than 0.1 percent to 1,814.36 at the close in Port
Louis. Namibia’s FTSE/Namibia Overall Index was little changed
at 858.55 in Windhoek.  Air Mauritius Ltd. (AML)  , sub-Saharan Africa’s fourth-
biggest airline, surged 4.6 percent to 11.5 rupees, the most
since April 9. Mauritius’s tourism ministry expects visitor
arrivals this year to increase 3.7 percent from 2011, more than
twice the growth rate set by the data agency, Minister Michael
Sik Yuen said.  Oando Plc (OANDO)  , a Nigerian energy company, climbed
for a second day, jumping by the 5 percent limit to 15.96 naira,
the biggest gain since Jan 11. Oil rose for a second day in  New
York , paring its fourth weekly decline, as German Chancellor
Angela Merkel left the door open to a compromise on debt sharing
in the euro area and after U.S. supplies rose to a 22-year high.  To contact the reporter on this story:
